d%20to%20spare%20room%20so%20at%20least%20one%20of%20us%20could%20get%20some%20decent%20sleep.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EWhile%20I'm%20fine%20with%20the%20choices%20we%20made%2C%20we%20didn't%20like%20feeling%20like%20roommates.%20%3C%2Fli%3E%3C%2Ful%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EFor%20nearly%20half%20a%20year%2C%20I%20chose%20to%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fco-sleeping-toddler-family-gets-more-rest-2024-9%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3Eshare%20my%20bed%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%3E%20with%20a%20male%20other%20than%20my%20husband%20%E2%80%94%20it%20was%20my%20youngest%20son.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EI%20kicked%20my%20husband%20out%20and%20into%20the%20spare%20room%20so%20I%20could%20co-sleep%20safely%20and%20comfortably%20with%20our%20second%20child%2C%20officially%20making%20us%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fsleep-divorce-marriage-separate-rooms-beds-2024-7%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3Esleep%20divorced%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%3E%20%E2%80%94%20something%20I%20never%20thought%20I'd%20do.%20It%20saved%20our%20sleep%20and%20sanity%20for%20a%20while%2C%20but%20when%20it%20ran%20its%20course%2C%20we%20had%20to%20be%20proactive%20about%20how%20we%20got%20back%20together%2C%20where%20we%20were%20meant%20to%20be.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%2239ac2c7c-03fd-4ddc-b905-d6e0f3db1759%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3E%3Cstrong%3EWith%20my%20first%20child%2C%20I%20was%20adamant%20that%20my%20husband%20had%20to%20suffer%20with%20me%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EBefore%20having%20kids%2C%20I%20never%20understood%20the%20appeal%20or%20need%20for%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fcosleeping-with-baby-toddler-child-husband-benefits-family-2023-6%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3Eco-sleeping%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%3E.%20Then%2C%20of%20course%2C%20I%20had%20kids.%20It%20was%20a%20long%20first%20year%20with%20my%20oldest%2C%20now%206%2C%20who%20didn't%20sleep%20through%20the%20night%20until%20he%20was%20just%20over%20a%20year%20old.%20I%20would%20fantasize%20about%20saying%20goodnight%20to%20him%20and%20not%20hearing%20another%20peep%20out%20of%20him%20until%207%20a.m.%2C%20but%20as%20it%20went%2C%20we%20would%20usually%20see%20each%20other%20at%20least%205%20times%20a%20night%2C%20if%20not%20more.%20So%20I'd%20give%20in%20and%20let%20him%20sleep%20next%20to%20me.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EDuring%20that%20time%2C%20I%20was%20adamant%20that%20my%20husband%20remain%20in%20our%20bed%2C%20to%20try%20to%20help%20share%20the%20load%20of%20soothing%20our%20nocturnally%20disgruntled%20son.%20It%20was%20mainly%20unsuccessful%2C%20but%20I%20wanted%20him%20there%20to%20provide%20solidarity%20and%20moral%20support.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%22d4b944f5-0062-4ef7-bfb9-70b7e9899978%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3E%3Cstrong%3EThe%20second%20time%20around%2C%20I%20had%20a%20change%20of%20heart%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EThose%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fnot-sleeping-health-effects-insomnia-2017-1%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Esleepless%20nights%3C%2Fa%3E%20felt%20like%20a%20distant%20memory%20by%20the%20time%20our%20second%20son%20came%20along%2C%20when%20our%20oldest%20was%20nearly%204.%20I'd%20heard%20about%20the%20fabled%20easier%20second%20baby%2C%20and%20in%20some%20ways%2C%20this%20was%20true.%20Our%20youngest%20slept%20for%20longer%20stretches%20at%20night%20than%20his%20night%20owl%20brother%20in%20the%20newborn%20phase.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThen%20it%20all%20changed%20at%20the%20textbook%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fguides%2Fparenting%2Ffour-months-sleep-regression%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3E4-month%20sleep%20regression%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%3Estage%2C%20dominated%20by%20my%20son's%20unquenchable%20appetite.%20He%20seemed%20to%20spend%20all%20night%20on%20my%20breast%2C%20dozing%20contentedly%20with%20a%20nipple%20in%20his%20mouth.%20It%20made%20me%20feel%20like%20I%20didn't%20really%20go%20to%20bed%2C%20that%20I%20was%20just%20clocking%20off%20from%20one%20shift%20to%20another%2C%20and%20simply%20changing%20out%20of%20day%20clothes%20and%20into%20pajamas.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EBut%20this%20time%2C%20with%20a%20demanding%20older%20kid%20to%20also%20take%20care%20of%2C%20I%20made%20the%20call%20to%20kick%20my%20husband%20out%20of%20our%20bed%2C%20and%20into%20the%20spare%20room.%20It%20didn't%20make%20sense%20for%20both%20of%20us%20to%20be%20exhausted%20when%20it%20was%20only%20me%20the%20baby%20wanted.%20At%20bedtime%2C%20we'd%20go%20our%20separate%20ways%2C%20me%20settling%20in%20for%20the%20night%20shift%2C%20and%20my%20husband%20looking%20forward%20to%20his%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fhow-to-get-better-sleep-millionaire-advice-2024-6%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3Erestful%2C%20uninterrupted%20night%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%3E%20%E2%80%94%20which%20I%20didn't%20begrudge%20him%20for%2C%20as%20he%20did%20(and%20still%20does)%20a%20lot%20of%20the%20heavy%20lifting%20during%20the%20day.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EWhile%20admittedly%20it%20was%20a%20little%20lonely%2C%20it%20made%20things%20slightly%20easier%20for%20me.%20Despite%20still%20having%20to%20soothe%20the%20baby%20multiple%20times%20a%20night%2C%20being%20just%20the%20two%20of%20us%20made%20it%20easier%20and%20safer%20to%20co-sleep.%20My%20quality%20of%20sleep%20was%20better%20as%20I%20wasn't%20uncomfortable%20sandwiched%20between%20the%20two%20people.%20And%20I%20wasn't%20disturbed%20every%20time%20my%20husband%20went%20to%20the%20bathroom%20or%20got%20up%20in%20the%20morning%2C%20nor%20was%20I%20anxious%20that%20his%20movements%20would%20wake%20the%20baby.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%2282b5fbbe-37ae-4941-b9cb-7610257b7ee0%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3E%3Cstrong%3EThe%20arrangement%20worked%20for%20us%20%E2%80%94%20until%20it%20didn't%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EWe%20even%20kept%20this%20arrangement%20during%20a%206-week%20working%20vacation%20in%20Greece%20that%20summer.%20Our%20youngest%20was%20then%208%20months%20and%20shared%20the%20main%20bedroom%20of%20our%20rental%20apartment%20with%20me%2C%20while%20my%20husband%20and%20our%204-year-old%20each%20took%20a%20single%20bed%20in%20the%20second%20room.%20While%20our%20setup%20helped%20me%20get%20as%20much%20rest%20as%20possible%20to%20enjoy%20that%20trip%2C%20that's%20when%20I%20really%20missed%20my%20husband%20the%20most.%20Despite%20being%20in%20a%20romantic%20vacation%20destination%2C%20there%20was%20very%20little%20romance%20going%20on.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EWhen%20we%20did%20get%20a%20chance%20to%20talk%2C%20we%20established%20that%20we%20were%20both%20ready%20to%20get%20back%20together.%20We%20recognized%20that%20we%20gave%20everything%20to%20our%20kids%20during%20the%20day%2C%20and%20that%20sleeping%20in%20the%20same%20bed%2C%20on%20our%20own%2C%20felt%20like%20the%20last%20space%20that%20was%20just%20for%20us.%20We%20were%20tired%20of%20feeling%20like%20co-parents%20and%20roommates%2C%20rather%20than%20two%20people%20in%20a%20loving%20relationship.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3ESo%20on%20our%20return%2C%20we%20put%20%26quot%3Boperation%20eviction%26quot%3B%20into%20place.%20It%20took%20some%20time%20and%20planning%2C%20but%20we%20eventually%20were%20able%20to%20adjust%20our%20sleeping%20arrangement.%20Around%2014%20months%2C%20our%20youngest%20started%20sleeping%20through%20the%20night%20and%20out%20of%20my%20bed%2C%20and%20my%20husband%20and%20I%20were%20able%20to%20find%20a%20place%20for%20our%20relationship%20again.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%22c090fdeb-a3af-46ed-8865-e7fdbcc9ae55%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3E%3Cstrong%3EWe%20prioritize%20our%20personal%20space%2C%20but%20know%20we%20can%20adjust%20when%20our%20kids%20need%20us%20to%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThe%20only%20time%20since%20our%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fseparate-bedrooms-couple-split-sleep-divorce-trend-2024-3%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3Esleep%20divorce%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%3E%20that%20my%20husband%20and%20I%20have%20slept%20apart%20was%20when%20our%20oldest%20had%20to%20spend%20a%20week%20in%20hospital%2C%20in%20April%202024%2C%20to%20be%20treated%20for%20a%20kidney%20infection.%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThat%20experience%20showed%20how%20resilient%20and%20adaptable%20we%20are%2C%20and%20committed%20to%20our%20kids.%20So%20we%20don't%20feel%20bad%20about%20being%20protective%20of%20our%20personal%20space%20the%20rest%20of%20the%20time%2C%20because%20when%20it%20counts%2C%20we%20are%20ready%20to%20step%20up.%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Cbr%3E%3Cbr%3E%3Cspan%3EThere%20was%20a%20period%20in%20our%20lives%20where%20sleep%20was%20a%20priority%20at%20the%20cost%20of%20our%20relationship%2C%20but%20after%20that%20chapter%2C%20it's%20time%20to%20prioritize%20ourselves%20again.%20Our%20sleep%20divorce%20days%20are%20behind%20us%2C%20and%20unless%20there's%20another%20medical%20emergency%20with%20one%20of%20our%20kids%2C%20I%20can't%20see%20them%20being%20in%20the%20cards%20again.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fparents-sleep-divorce-now-prioritizing-being-back-in-bed-together-2025-3%5C%22%3EBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1742393389000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F67dac64fb8b41a9673fb124e%3Fformat%3Djpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fparents-sleep-divorce-now-prioritizing-being-back-in-bed-together-2025-3%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%