_3_Union_Territories_of_India_2025-0%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ereport%20%3C%2Fa%3Ereleased%20by%20the%20Association%20for%20Democratic%20Reforms%20(ADR).%20Following%20him%20is%20Congress%20leader%20DK%20Shivakumar%2C%20the%20MLA%20from%20Karnataka's%20Kanakapura%2C%20with%20wealth%20exceeding%20Rs%201%2C413%20crore.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20ADR%20report%20is%20based%20on%20an%20analysis%20of%20self-sworn%20affidavits%20submitted%20by%20MLAs%20before%20contesting%20their%20latest%20elections.%20The%20study%20covered%204%2C092%20MLAs%20across%2028%20State%20Assemblies%20and%20three%20Union%20Territories%2C%20excluding%2024%20MLAs%20whose%20affidavits%20were%20unreadable%20and%20seven%20vacant%20assembly%20seats.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAt%20the%20bottom%20of%20the%20wealth%20spectrum%20is%20BJP%20MLA%20Nirmal%20Kumar%20Dhara%20from%20Indus%2C%20West%20Bengal%2C%20whose%20declared%20assets%20amount%20to%20just%20Rs%201%2C700.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EAmong%20the%20richest%20MLAs%2C%20notable%20figures%20include%3A%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EN.%20Chandrababu%20Naidu%2C%20Andhra%20Pradesh%20Chief%20Minister%3A%20Rs%20931%20crore%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EYS%20Jagan%20Mohan%20Reddy%2C%20former%20Andhra%20Pradesh%20Chief%20Minister%3A%20Rs%20757%20crore%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EKH%20Puttaswamy%20Gowda%2C%20Independent%20MLA%2C%20Karnataka%3A%20Rs%201%2C267%20crore%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EPriyakrishna%2C%20Congress%20MLA%2C%20Karnataka%3A%20Rs%201%2C156%20crore%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EP%20Narayana%2C%20TDP%20MLA%2C%20Andhra%20Pradesh%3A%20Rs%20824%20crore%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EV%20Prashanthi%20Reddy%2C%20TDP%20MLA%2C%20Andhra%20Pradesh%3A%20Rs%20716%20crore%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%3E%3Cimg%20alt%3D%5C%22Latest%20and%20Breaking%20News%20on%20NDTV%5C%22%20title%3D%5C%22Latest%20and%20Breaking%20News%20on%20NDTV%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fc.ndtvimg.com%2F2025-03%2F8t7gg3_adr-wealth-report_625x300_19_March_25.jpg%5C%22%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EPhot